                                                                  4731 1451
   The discrepancies between the reactivity worth measurements of 4731 1451
Dean et al.[De07] for Ag-109 and the WPEC evaluated file are +5%  4731 1451
and +2%  for  thermalized and PWR neutron spectra, respecyively.  4731 1451
 Assessment of the accuracy of the benchmark                      4731 1451
measurements indicated about 4% [De07]. Nevertheless, it was      4731 1451
decided to re-evaluate the Ag-109 file for possible               4731 1451
improvements below the  neutron fast energy region.               4731 1451
                                                                  4731 1451
 A recent activation measurement reported [Co01] a thermal        4731 1451
capture cross section of 72.9-+3.7 b for the ground transition    4731 1451
of Ag-110, implying a total thermal capture cross section of      4731 1451
76.8-+1.0 b for Ag109[Mu06]. This is quite inconsistent with the  4731 1451
recommended value of 91.0-+1.0 b, which is based on three         4731 1451
independent measurements, as well as consistenty checks of the    4731 1451
elemental and isotopic thermal values [Mu06].                     4731 1451
 A possible explanation for the large discrepancy of the          4731 1451
activation measurement may lie in a possible larger uncertainty,  4731 1451
about 20%, for the branching of the 657.5 keV gamma-ray.          4731 1451
 Because of these considerations, the adopted 2200m/sec capture   4731 1451
cross section is 90.23 b for a Westcott capture factor of         4731 1451
1.00857 [Mu06].                                                   4731 1451
